ency version bump.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Semver comparison correctly flags major version bumps as breaking changes.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: behavior is deterministic semver logic in one function/object boundary. REAL-INFRA/MOCK-HIDE: no external infra required. LLM-DEP/MULTI-STEP: none. Adversarial critique: if version parsing differs across upstream package-manager adapters, Integration may be needed. TOP2 contrast (Unit vs Integration): Unit wins because text is explicit semver comparison rule. Flip evidence: requirement that classification depends on adapter-specific normalized versions produced by other modules. REJECTION-GATE: rejected Integration because no cross-module or infra dependency is required by the behavior text.","test_description":"Table-driven semver cases (including pre-release/build metadata) asserting major increments are breaking and non-major increments are not.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.92,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"If breaking change is detected, scanner skips PR creation and emits a review flag in output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is orchestration/state handoff (breaking-change detector -> PR service gate -> report renderer). INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no required real OS/network/subprocess in behavior itself; PR client can be in-process spy, (b) no AI/ML output dependency, (c) no multi-agentic chain, (d) no LLM-involved stages. Adversarial critique: if skip logic only proved by asserting no real remote PR exists, System might be needed. TOP2 contrast (Integration vs System): Integration wins because behavior is control-flow gating plus output flag, testable with wired modules and fake PR a